<paragraph id="8BA5F2497952FF9EBEF47E8DCA8AFF6C" blockId="11.[151,1436,152,912]" box="[197,762,152,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
Size. Body length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7952FF9EBFAC7E8DC98AFF6C" box="[413,506,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity id="4CE25FAC7952FF9EBCA97E8DCA86FF6C" box="[664,758,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497952FF9EBEF47EABC915FEAD" blockId="11.[151,1436,152,912]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
Female. Frons slightly wider than anterior ocellus width; face narrower than frons, approximately one third anterior ocellus width. First hind tarsomere with one longer dorsal seta; hind tibia with pinnate scales on most of dorsal surface and ventrally on basal third. Wing wider than in male, more brown infuscated (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7952FF9EBB067F19CDFEFEF8" box="[1335,1422,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,254,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,465,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-203@10.[151,1436,437,1833]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus furcatus, n. sp., paratypes from Amazonas. A–F, male; A, wing; B, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; C, terminalia, lateral view; D, detail of posterior cercus; E, detail of posterior cercus in alternate view; F, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. G–I, female; G, wing; H, tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; I, sternite 8, ventral view; J, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: B–C,H–I = 0.2 mm; D,E,J = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321586" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321586/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
